qWat: QGIS Water Module

How to install
--------------

in your shell:

	$ git clone URL-to-this-module
	$ cd qWat
	$ 
	$ git submodule init
	$ git submodule update
        $
	$ cd qgis-plugin
	$ make
	$ 
	$ path_to_this_module=`pwd`
	$ cd ~/.qgis2/python/plugins
	$ ln -s "$path_to_this_module"
	$ 
	$ qgis &

Now go to the extensions menu and activate the qwat module.

Using the example project
-------------------------

You'll need to set up a postgres database first. Then in your shell:

	$ vim .pg_service.conf

The contents of the .pg_service.conf file should look like this:

	dbname=qwat
	user=THE_USER_THAT_WILL_RUN_QGIS
	port=5432
	host=localhost
	password=xxxxxxxx

Now create the qwat database in postgres:

	$ su - postgres
        $ psql
        postgres=# CREATE DATABASE qwat WITH ENCODING='UTF8' OWNER=THE_USER_THAT_WILL_RUN_QGIS CONNECTION LIMIT=-1;
        CREATE DATABASE
        postgres=#
        $ psql qwat
	qwat=# CREATE EXTENSION postgis;
	CREATE EXTENSION

now go to the 'data-model' directory and run the 'create_schemas.bash' script:

	$ cd data-model
        $ ./create_schemas.bash

in QGIS you should now be able to connect to the database by creating a new connection with
Name=qwat, Service=qwat, SSL mode=prefer.

If that works then open the qwat.qgs project in QGIS.

